{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"690dc32e-ef45-4d28-a5b0-f4b703770847","content":"I don't have a skill for **analyzing** crash dumps — the `dump-collect` skill only covers **collecting** them.\n\nHere's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Using `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\n# Install the tool\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n\n### Quick triage steps\n1. Run `pe` — often reveals the crash exception immediately\n2. Run `clrthreads` — look for threads with exceptions\n3. Run `clrstack` on the faulting thread\n\n### Alternatives\n- **Visual Studio** (Windows): File → Open → File, then select the `.dmp`\n- **WinDbg** (Windows): Load with SOS (`!analyze -v`)\n- **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n\nWould you like me to walk you through any of these steps, or do you have the dump file accessible here so I can try `dotnet-dump analyze` on it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5706dfff-dfce-4bcd-9b0a-9813a69a3bcf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me check if there's a relevant skill available for this task.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for configuring and collecting crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstones\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple crash logs\n\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing crash dumps, so I'll need to help the user directly with guidance on how to analyze their dump file.","outputTokens":554,"requestId":"6800:2D9A4B:2D3C9C9:3200594:69FD42F7"},"id":"28349f21-2ef1-41fa-a7df-455a87c18cee","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:57:25.480Z","parentId":"805b194a-b33d-4e7d-8d4a-3b4da2eecda9"}
